This paper deals with scheduling in 5G wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization and control aspects, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of minislots and superposition/puncturing techniques, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
